&lt;p&gt;NEW YORK - Yahoo slashed the price of the sale of its core Internet business to Verizon by $350 million following a pair of major data breaches at &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.nationmultimedia.com/news/breakingnews/30306894&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.nationmultimedia.com/news/breakingnews/30306894&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Healthcare data breaches reach a &amp;lsquo;sizeable number of US consumers&amp;rsquo;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The global professional services company also found that half of the victims of data breaches had suffered from medical identity theft  a crime that &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.welivesecurity.com/2017/02/21/healthcare-data-breaches-reach-sizeable-number-us-consumers/&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.welivesecurity.com/2017/02/21/healthcare-data-breaches-reach-sizeable-number-us-consumers/&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

