&lt;p&gt;Yahoo slashed the price of its core Internet business in the sale to Verizon by $350 million following a pair of major data breaches at Yahoo, the two &amp;hellip;  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.dailysabah.com/business/2017/02/22/verizon-cuts-yahoos-price-by-350-million-after-data-breaches&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.dailysabah.com/business/2017/02/22/verizon-cuts-yahoos-price-by-350-million-after-data-breaches&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Verizon&amp;rsquo;s $350 million discount on Yahoo purchase shows cost of breaches is&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IT World Canada For CISOs, the readjusted terms of the deal are likely of interest because it demonstrates how the market puts a real cost on data breaches.  &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.itworldcanada.com/article/verizons-350-million-discount-on-yahoo-purchase-shows-cost-of-breaches-is-real/390853&#34; onclick=&#34;trackOutboundLink(&#39;http://www.itworldcanada.com/article/verizons-350-million-discount-on-yahoo-purchase-shows-cost-of-breaches-is-real/390853&#39;); return false;&#34;&gt;more&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

